name: Quut - Triplet
description:
The Triplet is a unique, multi-functional toy that is easy and fun to use. 

It’s part shovel, to help kids dig holes, build foundations and carve out moats. 

It’s part sand sifter, to help remove shells and other sediment for smooth, shapeable sand. And it’s part rake, to let kids create extra designs. 

The hollow handle can even be used as water funnel to finish off the coolest sandcastles ever with sand art! 

Your child will love the Triplet by Quut – we wish we’d had one when we were kids!
 
 
 
Available in three great colours: Mellow Yellow, Calypso Pink and Lagoon Green.
 
Dimensions: 18.3 cm x 17.2 cm x 24.5 cm (approximately)

name: Quut - Ballo
description:
We know – it doesn’t even look like a bucket. 

But your kids will use it like one, and that’s what makes the Ballo so unique. 

Its smart design and soft-touch finishing makes it easy to grab water, run up the beach, and pour with ease. 

Its spherical shape is also surprisingly stable, resulting in minimal spills. 

Carrying water from the sea to a sandcastle has never been this much fun. 

 
Ballo is available in two funky colours: Calypso Pink and Lagoon Green.
 
Dimensions: 19 cm x 19 cm x 19 cm (approximately)

name: Quut - Scoppi - Lagoon Green
description:
The Scoppi immediately attracts the eye with its exciting, iconic design. 

Kids will love it as they use both their hands and their feet to move sand around the beach with ease. 

It even comes with a smart detachable sand sifter that will double the fun as they build forts, moats and castles…we bet they’ll bury you up to your toes in no time!

(Hint: the Scoppi is a perfect snow toy too!)
 
 
 
Scoppie comes in Lagoon Green/Mellow Yellow combo.
 
Dimensions: 65.5 cm x 16.5 cm x 2.7 cm (approximately)

name: Door Jam - Children’s Height Chart
description:
The slimmest most unobtrusive height chart in childhood history, at only 30mm wide! 

Door Jam, came out of a simple desire to stop people drawing all over their door frames in order to record the heights of their children! 

Doorjam is self-adhesive and comes in 3 jam colours - Strawberry and Raspberry and Blueberry. 

It measures 30mm x 2100mm high, and can be trimmed to suit height of position chosen. 

Of course Doorjam can fit anywhere, not just on a door jamb but also on the edge of doors, mirrors, inside wardrobes, anywhere a flat surface can be found. It is removeable but not repositionable.

There is room to record names and dates of growth spurts with pencil, biro or permanent marker and the packaging is made from brilliant glass clear recycled PET to please the environment.

Doorjam is Australian Made and designed.

name: Small Parts Kit
description:
We have created a small parts kit for your already loved iconic tram or iconic ferry. We wanted to give you some extra bits to extend your play!
 
Our kids were writing tickets and giving passengers fines because they did not have ticket. We loved watching them play with their iconic tram and iconic ferry for years and thought our kids had a great idea with creating tickets. We also lost many passengers so thought it might be a grand idea to put all these things for you in a small parts kit - ready to play with.
 
We have included the following for you.
 
x5 extra passengers (painted more posh and detailed to make them really stand out)
 x4 pretend coins 
x2 pretend money notes 
x1 tram ticket (not a MYKI we gave you a ticket old school style!) 
x1 ferry ticket 
x1 give way sign

all wood pieces which include x5 passengers + x4 coins + x2notes + x2 tickets + x3 signs

Each biscuit is made of wood and makes a great accessory to any tea party or kitchen set. We included numbers on the reverse of each biscuit to make learning one to ten yum! And we like things neat to we also have the handy beautiful tin to pack them all away in afterwards.

This book also… Contains no photoshopped and over-styled baby photos (because it’s just about your child) Is gender-neutral and stylish enough not to embarrass them later (although the things you write down might!) Includes space for both mum’s and dad’s experience (because fathers are important too) Lets you record the thoughts of a modern extended family (rather than just four grandparents) Means you never need to feel guilty about forgetting when they got the last 18 teeth (because you can just take that page out) Hardback – 56 pages, designed in Australia.
